---
layout: default
title: Features
suppress_header: true
extra_css:
  - features.css
extra_js:
  - libs/jquery.magnific-popup.min.js
---
.wrapper
  %nav#qnav.navbar.navbar-default.qnav.hidden-xs.qnav2{role: "navigation"}
    .container-fluid.featurenav
      %ul.nav.nav-pills.nav-justified
        %li
          %a{href: "#community"} Community Edition
        %li
          %a{href: "#enterprise"} Enterprise Edition
        %li
          %a{href: "#compare"} Compare
  #community.wide-feature.head
    .container
      .row
        .col-sm-12.col-md-8.head-non-bg
          .title
            GitLab
            %br
            %b Community edition
          .header-text
            %ul
              %li
                %b> Feature rich
                \: Git repository management, code reviews, issue tracking, activity feeds and wikis. It comes with
                %a{href: "/gitlab-ci/"} GitLab CI
                for continuous integration and delivery.
              %li
                %b> Open Source
                \: MIT licensed, community driven, 700+ contributors, inspect and modify the source, easy to integrate into your infrastructure
              %li
                %b> Scalable
                \: support 25,000 users on one server or a highly available active/active cluster
            .actions
              %a.btn.btn-default.btn-lg{href: "/downloads"} Download
              %a.btn.btn-default.btn-lg{href: "https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab-ce/tree/master#README"} Source + Readme
            %br
            If you want to use GitLab without installing it,
            check out
            %a{href: "/gitlab-com"} GitLab.com
            Note that only self-hosted GitLab will let you integrate with your LDAP.
        .col-md-4.head-bg.hidden-sm.hidden-xs
  .container
    .row.feature-row
      .col-md-4.small-feature
        .name
          ACTIVITY
          %b STREAM
        %a.image-link{href: "/images/feature_page/activity_stream_full.png"}
          = image_tag "/images/feature_page/activity_stream_full.png", class: "img-responsive"
        .link
          %a{href: "https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab-ce/activity"} Have a look at an actual activity page
      .col-md-4.small-feature
        .name
          FILE
          %b BROWSER
        %a.image-link{href: "/images/feature_page/file_browser_full.png"}
          = image_tag "/images/feature_page/file_browser_full.png", class: "img-responsive"
        .link
          %a{href: "https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab-ce/tree/master"} Try navigating GitLab's code
      .col-md-4.small-feature
        .name
          GIT POWERED
          %b WIKI
        %a.image-link{href: "/images/feature_page/wiki_full.png"}
          = image_tag "/images/feature_page/wiki_full.png", class: "img-responsive"
  .wide-feature.mr
    .row
      .col-md-12
        .name
          powerful
          %b code review
        .description
          Merge requests with line-by-line comments, CI and issue tracker integrations and much more..
      .wide-img
        %a.image-link{href: "/images/feature_page/mr_sh.png"}
          = image_tag "/images/feature_page/mr_sh.png", class: "img-responsive"
      .wide-feature-link
        %a.btn-default{href: "https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab-ce/merge_requests"} See the power of merge requests on GitLab.com
  .container
    .row.feature-row
      .col-md-4.small-feature
        .name
          ISSUE
          %b MANAGEMENT
        %a.image-link{href: "/images/feature_page/issue_management.png"}
          = image_tag "/images/feature_page/issue_management.png", class: "img-responsive"
        .link
          %a{href: "https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab-ce/issues"} See how we use issues to manage our open source project
      .col-md-4.small-feature
        .name
          CODE
          %b SNIPPETS
        %a.image-link{href: "/images/feature_page/snippets_full.png"}
          = image_tag "/images/feature_page/snippets_full.png", class: "img-responsive"
      .col-md-4.small-feature
        .name
          WEB
          %b HOOKS
        %a.image-link{href: "/images/feature_page/webhooks_full.png"}
          = image_tag "/images/feature_page/webhooks_full.png", class: "img-responsive"
  #enterprise.wide-feature.head.ee
    .container
      .name
        gitlab
        %b enterprise edition
      .description
        %p
          GitLab Enterprise Edition builds on top of the Community Edition and includes extra features mainly aimed at organizations with more than 100 users.
        %p
          It has LDAP group sync, audit logs and multiple roles.
          It includes deeper authentication and authorization integration, has fine-grained workflow management, has extra server management options and it integrates with your tool stack.
          GitLab EE runs on your servers, for our SaaS offering please see
          %a{href: "/gitlab-com"} GitLab.com
        %p
          = link_to "Download GitLab Enterprise Edition", "https://about.gitlab.com/downloads-ee"
  .container
    .row.feature-row
      .col-md-4.small-feature
        .name
          GIT
          %b HOOKS
        %a.image-link{href: "/images/feature_page/githooks_full.png"}
          = image_tag "/images/feature_page/githooks_full.png", class: "img-responsive"
      .col-md-4.small-feature
        .name
          LDAP
          %b GROUP SYNC
        %a.image-link{href: "/images/feature_page/ldap_groups_full.png"}
          = image_tag "/images/feature_page/ldap_groups_full.png", class: "img-responsive"
      .col-md-4.small-feature
        .name
          REPOSITORY
          %b MIRRORING
        %a.image-link{href: "/images/feature_page/mirror.png"}
          = image_tag "/images/feature_page/mirror.png", class: "img-responsive"
        .link
          %a{href: "http://docs.gitlab.com/ee/workflow/repository_mirroring.html"}
            Read about repository mirroring
= partial "includes/features/gitlab-ee-trial"
